HEADWORD: monkey pod
<hw>monkey pod</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<def>large ornamental tropical American tree (<spn>Albizia saman</spn>)
with bipinnate leaves and globose clusters of flowers with crimson
stamens and sweet-pulp seed pods eaten by cattle.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> rain tree, saman, zaman, zamang, <spn>Albizia
saman</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monkey-pot</ent>⟦br⟧
